@begin(section)
@title(Templates)

Codex ships with two templates, @b(Minima) and @b(Gamma).

@begin(section)
@title(Minima)

@image[src="minima.png"]()

Minima is, as the name implies, a minimalist theme. It's name in manifest files
is @c(:minima).

@end(section)

@begin(section)
@title(Gamma)

@image[src="gamma.png"]()

Gamma is the template you're looking at. It's inspired by the
@link[uri="https://stripe.com/docs"](Stripe documentation).

You can use it by setting @c(:template) to @c(:gamma) in manifest.

@end(section)

@end(section)
